		Coastland's founder, Derek Dunn, has 20+ years of successfully managing portfolios throughout various market cycles while at major investment management firms.  Complementing his experience is a seasoned investment team with a long history of working together.  Of its 21 total employees, Coastland has 13 investment professionals including four portfolio managers.  Each of the portfolio managers has 10+ years of investment experience.

		 





Derek Dunn

Chief Investment Officer, Founding Partner

  			Over 20 years of industry experience, trading and managing complex derivative portfolios.   			Managed a proprietary portfolio within the Securities Investment Group at Wells Fargo.   			Co-founder of KBC Alternative Investments and Head of US investments for their multi billion dollar credit & convertible strategies funds.    			Winner of two Eurohedge Fund Awards.   			Profitably traded relative value strategies throughout every stage of the equity and credit market cycles for D.E. Shaw and Marin Capital.   			BA from the University of Stirling, UK (1993)    







Peter Sterling

President

 		15 years of industry experience managing credit and derivative portfolios. 		Portfolio Manager for the Coastland Direct Yield Fund, a vehicle which purchases consumer loan and small business related assets. 		Profitably invested against defaulted pools of loans including credit card receivables in the small business and consumer space as well as managing servicers of NPL Pools.    		Former portfolio manager at KBC Alternative Investments and Marin Capital within the credit arbitrage markets.   Previously hired into D.E. Shaw/KBC F.P. to trade derivatives.  		BA from Cornell University, double major in economics and psychology (1998).




  







