Bank/fintech partnerships
The shift from the siloed model of banks and fintech companies working separately to a continually collaborative model, creating the “best of both worlds” (including potential regulatory changes like proposed CFPB rules and the OCC’s fintech charter; and independent changes, like the increasing number of partnerships between banks and fintech companies, banks creating “fintech” products like Goldman Sachs’ Marcus, etc.)





