Panelist
Compliance Specialist, AutoGravity Corporation






The Future of Alternative Lending

2016 was a year of surprises (tumultuous start, etc).  What most surprised you about 2016 and what developments of 2016 do you believe have had the biggest impact on shaping our industry ?
Which sectors of alt lending have had the most dramatic change (growth and/or decline) across P2P, SMB, Real Estate, other
The Customer:  Are alternative lenders fundamentally using new technology and data to transform how service is delivered to the customer, or, are they just originating loans differently.  Which lenders and sectors have fundamentally transformed the customer experience?  Do you think this innovation in customer experience is here to stay/what will it take for it to become mainstream?
Economy:  What is the broader impact of Alt Lending on the economy – is it opening up access to funding to more people, other impact?
Traditional FI/Banks:   Partnerships between fin tech & banks has been the big buzz word of 2016.  Who is doing this right and do any of them really have traction or is this just about PR?
What are your predictions for 2017?





